<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
Shell oblique-heliciform, white, and translucent; whorls 6; spire convex with distinct suture. Shell surface glossy with fine transverse ridges that diminish below periphery. Embryonic shell ~ 
<normalizedToken originalValue="2½">21/2</normalizedToken>
whorls with smooth surface; following whorls regularly coiled. Shell periphery rounded; last whorl axially deflected. Aperture semi-ovate; peristome continuous; sometimes discontinuous, thin, expanded, and slightly reflected. Apertural dentition with one strong parietal lamella. Umbilicus open and deep (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. A-C Haploptychius blanfordi A syntype NHMUK 1888.12.4.777 - 779 from Pegu with apertural dentition B specimen NHMUK 1906.2.2.338 from Akouktoung, Pegu C specimen NHMUK 1909.3.15.71 from Pegu D Haploptychius burmanicus, syntype NHMUK 1906.2.2.199 from Tongoop, Arakan with apertural dentition." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1110.85399.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/710475" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">10D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanford" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Haploptychius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploptychius burmanicus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="burmanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Haploptychius burmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still known only from the type locality in southern Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation author="Blanford, WT" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" refId="B8" refString="Blanford, WT, 1865. Contributions to Indian Malacology. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 34: 81, 82." title="Contributions to Indian Malacology. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 34: 81, 82." year="1865">Blanford 1865</bibRefCitation>
). Outside Myanmar, it is also reported from Mizoram in India (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramakrishna, Mitra SC" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 359" refId="B69" refString="Ramakrishna, Mitra SC, Dey, A, 2010. Annotated checklist of Indian land molluscs. Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper 306: 1 - 359" title="Annotated checklist of Indian land molluscs." volume="306" year="2010">Ramakrishna et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
); however, this record needs to be verified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
This species highly resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. blanfordi" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="blanfordi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. blanfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shell form, but 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. burmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="burmanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. burmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more globosely heliciform, with a higher spire and only one parietal lamella. Without anatomical information, the generic placement of this species is still tentative, and we retain this as 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" author="Blanford, WT" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" refId="B10" refString="Blanford, WT, Godwin-Austen, HH, 1908. The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae. Taylor and Francis, London, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" title="The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" year="1908">Blanford and Godwin-Austen (1908)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. perlissus" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="perlissus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. perlissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" author="Vermeulen, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Folia Malacologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="7 - 41" refId="B95" refString="Vermeulen, JJ, Luu, HT, Theary, K, Anker, K, 2019. New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda and Pulmonata) of the Mekong Delta Limestone Hills (Cambodia, Vietnam). Folia Malacologica 27 (1): 7 - 41, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" title="New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda and Pulmonata) of the Mekong Delta Limestone Hills (Cambodia, Vietnam)." url="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" volume="27" year="2019">Vermeulen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
from Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" author="Vermeulen, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Folia Malacologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="7 - 41" refId="B95" refString="Vermeulen, JJ, Luu, HT, Theary, K, Anker, K, 2019. New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda and Pulmonata) of the Mekong Delta Limestone Hills (Cambodia, Vietnam). Folia Malacologica 27 (1): 7 - 41, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" title="New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda and Pulmonata) of the Mekong Delta Limestone Hills (Cambodia, Vietnam)." url="https://doi.org/10.12657/folmal.027.001" volume="27" year="2019">Vermeulen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
: figs 49-51) can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. burmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="burmanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. burmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having an oblique-ovate shell, less extended penultimate whorl from the last whorl, lower to nearly flattened spire, the palatal side is almost straight, basal side rounded, and columellar side broadly rounded, whereas 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. burmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="burmanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. burmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a higher spire, more compressed shell, and the last whorl is more axially deflected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
